<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n56197g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n56" href="#n56197g">N56 (VI.B.41)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n56all.htm#n56197g"> 197(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> chief epic hero</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The paramount <mark>chief</mark> of early Britain <font color="green">[King Arthur]</font>, whose prowess and conquests form the prime <mark>epic</mark> theme of Geoffrey <font color="green">[<i>History</i>]</font> and Layamon, appears as the king of no known realm, numbering among his retainers <mark>heroic</mark> figures drawn from the uttermost limits of the mythical world. <small> W. Lewis Jones, <a name="WJKA5" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#WJKA5"><cite title="source">King Arthur in History and Legend</cite></a> (1914) 95</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
